|GKB-- Miscellaneous Druid Commands ------------------------------|000

    Guild commands live under /cmds/guilds/druid/ (dhelp, dchat,
druids, dscore, dhist, dtitle, resettitle, resettitlealt, nwyfre,
ritual, etc.) and /cmds/guilds/druid/spells/ (active invocations
and grove utility commands). See |CKBdhelp general|000 for the full help
menu.

|CKBattune|000 - Read the terrain(s) of the immediate area.

|CKBdhist <#>|000 - List recent messages on the druid channel.  <#>
   is the number of lines it goes back, with a maximum of 300
   and a default of 30.

|CKBdscore|000 - List your druid score report. This includes available
   study slots, learned powers, grove status, and material guidance.

|CKBdtitle|000 - Changes your title on the |CKBdruids|000 report.

|CKBresettitle|000 - Changes your title to your Druid guild title (the
   one you get when you advance guild level).  This is not the
   title on the |CKBdruids|000 report, but the title used in |CKBwho|000,
   |CKBfinger|000, and other places.

|CKBresettitlealt|000 - Changes your title to a more feminine version of
   your Druid guild title, eg. 'mistress' instead of 'master'.

|CKBdruids|000 (also |CKBdwho|000) - Lists all druids on the mud, along with
   a status report.  The status codes are:
   D - dead
   E - wiz+ editing a file
   F - fighting
   I - input mode (reading, writing, listing 'who', etc.)
   M - muffed
   [Idle] - idle

|CKBdruids2|000 - Much like |CKBdruids|000, just a different format.
